        <!-- Section 7: Lesson 4 -->
        <div id="section7" class="section">
            <h2>Section 4: Cleaning Techniques</h2>
            <p>A systematic approach makes cleaning more effective.</p>
            <p>Here’s how:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><i class="fas fa-broom"></i> Start with dry cleaning—sweep or dust before mopping or wiping.</li>
                <li><i class="fas fa-arrow-down"></i> Work from top to bottom, starting with ceilings and ending with floors.</li>
                <li><i class="fas fa-tools"></i> Use the right method for each surface, like floors or windows.</li>
                <li><i class="fas fa-vacuum"></i> Choose proper tools like industrial vacuums or microfiber cloths.</li>
            </ul>
            <button onclick="prevSection()">Back</button>
            <button onclick="nextSection()">Next</button>
