        <!-- Section 11: Lesson 6 -->
        <div id="section11" class="section">
            <h2>Section 6: Cleaning Walls and Ceilings</h2>
            <p>Walls and ceilings gather dust and need care.</p>
            <p>Follow these steps:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><i class="fas fa-broom"></i> Start with dry dusting using a microfiber cloth or duster.</li>
                <li><i class="fas fa-sponge"></i> For stains, use a mild cleaner and sponge gently.</li>
                <li><i class="fas fa-spider"></i> Look for cobwebs in corners and use an extendable duster.</li>
                <li><i class="fas fa-tint-slash"></i> Don’t over-wet—too much water can harm drywall.</li>
            </ul>
            <button onclick="prevSection()">Back</button>
