        <!-- Section 13: Lesson 7 -->
        <div id="section13" class="section">
            <h2>Section 7: Cleaning Windows and Glass</h2>
            <p>Windows should be streak-free and spotless.</p>
            <p>Here’s how:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><i class="fas fa-broom"></i> Dust off first with a dry cloth or vacuum attachment.</li>
                <li><i class="fas fa-spray-can"></i> Spray glass cleaner and wipe with a lint-free cloth.</li>
                <li><i class="fas fa-window-maximize"></i> Clean frames and sills with a damp cloth.</li>
                <li><i class="fas fa-sun"></i> Avoid cleaning in direct sunlight—it dries the cleaner too fast and leaves streaks.</li>
            </ul>
            <button onclick="prevSection()">Back</button>
            <button onclick="nextSection()">Next</button>
