        <!-- Section 19: Lesson 10 -->
        <div id="section19" class="section">
            <h2>Section 10: Cleaning Doors and Doorframes</h2>
            <p>Doors and doorframes collect dust and smudges.</p>
            <p>Here’s how to clean them:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><i class="fas fa-broom"></i> Dust first with a microfiber cloth.</li>
                <li><i class="fas fa-sponge"></i> Wipe with mild soap and a damp cloth for marks or stains.</li>
                <li><i class="fas fa-door-closed"></i> Polish doorknobs and hinges with a metal cleaner if needed.</li>
                <li><i class="fas fa-tint"></i> Dry well to avoid water damage to wood or metal.</li>
            </ul>
            <button onclick="prevSection()">Back</button>
